The Community Asset Portal (CAP)


\n

The Community Asset Portal (CAP) is a web application that shows an up-to-date map of social services such as shelters
column305: and mental health and youth support services. The app detects the location of users and allows them to see the resources using a colour-coded map or by moving through a list of categories
column306: such as Health or Food & Housing services. It also shows people how to get to the location by car
column308:
as well as gives contact information.

\n

It was developed by Ryerson Geography students in collaboration with Business Intelligence
column309:
the City of Toronto and using data provided by 2-1-1 Toronto.

"}}
